cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about using neural networks for Chinese word segmentation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep stacking framework, which involves integrating models from different domains, and this could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian-based models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on low-resource datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as this sub-category often deals with the challenges of working with limited data.
